      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "I have the same problem on Windows 2003 using v0.8. It appears that the shortcut in \"%USERPROFILE%\\Start Menu\\Programs\\Startup\" is being removed and recreated each time that Bitcoin starts up. This effectively removes all existing command line parameters in the Target field of the shortcut and reverts the shortcut back to the default. I tried setting the shortcut to read-only, hoping that the process of reverting it would then fail gracefully, but this causes a fatal error in the client when it is unable to remove the existing shortcut.\n",
